  "reference": "Numerics @ a2c4dbf. Args conventions (this port's own -- see fixtures/README.md): Fourier.fft_at/real_fft_at take args = [data..., inverse(0/1), index] (n = len(args)-2); Fourier.correlation_at takes args = [data1..., data2..., index] (equal-length data1/data2, n = (len(args)-1)/2); Fourier.autocorrelation_at takes args = [series..., lag_max, lag] (n = len(args)-2; lag_max == -1 triggers the default auto-lag floor(min(10*log10(n), n-1))). The correlation_at and autocorrelation_explicit_lagmax cases have no upstream C# test literal (Test_FFT_Correlation only cross-checks Fourier.Autocorrelation against Autocorrelation.Function, no hardcoded literal), so their expected values were generated by running the case's inputs through tools/oracle_emitter --dump against the REAL C# Numerics library and confirming the printed actuals reproduce via verify_oracles.py.",
